rComments: He repeated his question a copule times and I still could not grasp what he was trying to ask. I agreed with all other posters. I wonder how he got to where he is now.

Prof Katz means well, but he is a horrible professor. Lecturesreading plan were hugely disorganizedillogical. Lecture pace was painfully slow. Some reading assignments were never mentioned in class. Very monotone & didn't try to promote enthusiasm or class discussion. Rare instances he did ask questions, they'd make no sense. Awkward silences.

Katz is a good guy and makes a genuine effort to engage students. Unfortunately, he fails miserably while attempting to do so. His language  barrier prevents him from properly understanding students' questions. He would fail as a litigator, since he can't get the point. Though he's probably brilliant, he is an utter organizational mess.

Professor Katz is not a good teacher. I think he cares, as he tries to engage students, but he can't really do it. He has a hard time understanding what you are trying to say, and if it isn't worded exactly as he is thinking about it, he doesn't get it. It is unfortunately partially a language barrier (he is from Israel) but it makes class painful.
